<br>
Epic weapons = Kunark Era<br>
Veeshan's Peak = Kunark's &quot;Ending&quot; Keyed dungeon<br>
<br>
PoSky = Original (late original, pre kunark) Era<br>
<br>
No epic pieces have ever dropped in Veeshan's Peak, which is essentially the &quot;End of the Expansion&quot; for Kunark, same era as our Epic weapons. Rather, it's the end of the expansion 'prior', the Plane of Sky, that seems to be the most difficult to nagivate.<br>
<br>
Rather, I figure the quests were originally designed to help us inside the end of the expansion (VP), rather than be located within it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=artulyn1>Artulyn1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 167<br> <font color=#333333>(11/5/02 7:36:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=391.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: comment</span><hr size=1> PoS opened up a few months before Kunark did, I remember all of the path exploits and lev exploits that were used before they fixed it so you couldn't use any form of lev and had all of your buffs stripped when you zoned in to make sure you didn't have DMF when you zoned in.<br>
<br>
I don't think anybody made it past the 4th or 5th island until after kunark came out and people got high enough to cast on some of the mobs. Believe me it was quite an accomplishment to kill the efreeti lord with just level 46 to 50 characters. So while CR does have some bad information, this is not one of them.<br>
<br>
<br>
As for epic/particle weapons, VI originally called all of them particle weapons and referred to the quests to obtain them as epic quests. They also stated that not everyone would get one or be able to get one and they would always be rare &amp; badges of honor. However the players kept calling the weapons &quot;epic weapons&quot; and the people at VI eventually started calling them epics as well. <p><br>
Artulyn Starsummoner Arch Mage<br>
